  "title": "Associate Pastor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong>: The Associate Pastor is responsible for shepherding God’s people at our church through the ministry of word and prayer. He is expected to lead a Congregation at our church and its staff team, be involved in service planning and leading, preaching, training small group leaders, leading Bible Studies, discipling men 1-1, and sharing the gospel with people. In addition, this will involve some administration especially in terms of planning for the pastoral care of the Congregation, and where necessary, providing biblical counselling. He will have to oversee the well-being of singles, married couples, and families, and work to mature each of these groups in their understanding and application of Scripture to their particular life role.</p><p>The Associate Pastor serves under the leadership and guidance of our Elders.<br /></p><p><strong>Qualifications</strong>: Associate Pastors typically have completed some form of formal theological education (Bible College or Ministry Training). Depending on the qualifications of the individual, our Elders will draw up a personalised training programme to ensure ongoing personal and professional development. In accordance with 1 Tim 3:1-7, Associate Pastors would be expected to be gifted Bible teachers who are above reproach in their private life, family life, and public life.</p><p><strong>Application process: </strong>Thank you for your application and interest in this role. Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p>",
